QUETTA, Pakistan Thousands of government workers and their families have evacuated a remote town in southwestern Pakistan, a senior official said, amid fears of renewed fighting between renegade tribesmen and security forces after clashes left at least 30 people dead.
Interior Minister Aftab Khan Sherpao told reporters in the capital, Islamabad, that tribal fighters were digging in around Dera Bugti and destroying roads.
17 minority Hindus were killed during fighting between tribesmen and troops in tense Pakistani town, official says.
